@startuml
scale 1
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 80
skinparam BoxPadding 40

actor "User" as U
participant "Web\nApplication" as W
participant "Backend\nAPI" as B
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

== Metrics Tab - Page Load ==

U -> W: Navigate to /scorecards
W -> W: Read active team\nfrom Zustand

W -> B: GET /weeks
B -> DB: Query last 13 weeks
DB -> B: Week list
B -> W: WeekResponse[]

W -> W: Determine current week

W -> B: GET /metrics\n?teamId=X&weekId=W
B -> B: @PreAuthorize\nteam membership check
B -> DB: Query metrics for team
DB -> B: Metric entities
B -> DB: Query metric values\n(current + previous week)
DB -> B: MetricValue entities
B -> B: Map metrics with values\nand goal status
B -> W: MetricResponse[]
W -> W: Calculate goal-met\nindicators
W -> U: Display scorecard table

== Update Weekly Value ==

U -> W: Enter value in cell
W -> B: PUT /metric-values\n{metricId, weekId, value}
B -> B: Validate team membership
B -> DB: UPSERT metric_value\n(insert or update)
DB -> B: Updated value
B -> W: MetricValueResponse
W -> W: Invalidate query cache
W -> U: Show value with\ngoal indicator

== Create Metric ==

U -> W: Fill metric form + submit
W -> B: POST /metrics\n{teamId, name, goal,\nunit, operator, ownerId}
B -> B: Validate team membership
B -> B: Validate owner in team
B -> DB: INSERT metric
DB -> B: Saved metric
B -> W: MetricResponse
W -> U: New metric in scorecard

== Trends Tab ==

U -> W: Switch to "Trends" tab
W -> B: GET /metrics/trends\n?teamId=X
B -> B: Validate team membership
B -> DB: Query all team metrics
B -> DB: Query metric values\nacross 13 weeks
DB -> B: Values grouped by\nmetric and week
B -> B: Build trend data points
B -> W: TrendsTabMetricListResponse\n{metrics: [{id, name,\ndata: [{week, value}]}]}
W -> W: Render with Recharts
W -> U: Display trend table/chart

== Background: Week Creation ==

note over B,DB: WeekCreationScheduler\n(Monday 00:01)
B -> DB: INSERT week IF NOT EXISTS\n(startDate=Mon, endDate=Sun)
DB -> B: New or existing week

@enduml
